<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-603-735  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 603 735.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Computers  Oct 1990 v39 n10 p1291(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computing cumulative measures of stiff Markov chains usingaggregation. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bobbio, Andrea; Trivedi, Kishor.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Cumulative or integral measures are a new class of measures thatshow a system's operational characteristics over a finiteinterval, not at a fixed time instant or in steady-state.andP;  Anaggregation method to compute the transient cumulative measure oflarge, stiff Markov models is developed.andP;  Classification of thestates of the original problem into slow, fast transient, and fastrecurrent states is the basis for this method.andP;  Results show thata better characterization of the time dependent system behaviorcan be provided by cumulative measures.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Markov ProcessQueueing NetworksReliabilityModelsTransient StateFault Tolerance.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Markov transition graph. (chart)Aggregated Markov chain. (chart)Queueing network model of an interactive system. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>